
Task
Find the modulus of a number without using the Math.abs (x) method.

Find the modulus of the number x without using the Math.abs (x) method.
Write a function called absValue that takes a number x as an argument and returns the modulus of that number. Solve this problem without using the Math.abs (x) method.
Examples:
• the absValue (-1) function must return 1;
• the absValue (5) function must return 5;
• the absValue (0) function must return 0.

Solution
function absValue (x) {
  if (x> 0) return x;
     else if (x <0) return -x;
       else
return 0;
}
